#start
  span.intro EmacsFood is an archive an Emacs Lisp meta-packages.
    :markdown
      ### What is are EmacsFood meta-packages?

      A meta-package is basically a plain old ELPA package, except it's purpose is to
      install and configure a number of other regular ELPA packages.

      Conceptually they are similar to (and inspired by) Spacemacs configuration layers.

      For example, the Spacemacs git layer would be comparable to the
      EmacsFood git meta-package, and vice-versa. They may or may not
      provide the same packages / defaults.

