      aspect of Emacs, exist and are easily interchanged by switching
      between similar meta-packages.

      ## Starter Kits and Shared Emacs Configs

      If you are thinking about, or currently provide a shared config,
      or starter kit for Emacs. We also encourage you to consider
      providing it as a meta-package (or collection of meta-packages)
      either here on EmacsFood or on your own ELPA server. Feel free
      to fork us.

      ## About EmacsFood

      EmacsFood is **Fully compatible** with `package.el` and
      [ELPA](http://tromey.com/elpa/) and is **Open source**, so [you
      can help improve it](https://github.com/emacsfodder/emacsfood/)

  span.intro To start using EmacsFood,
    :markdown
      - Use with Emacs 24.x and up.
      - Add to your `package-archives` list:

              (add-to-list 'package-archives '("emacsfood" . "http://#{hostname}/packages/"))

